ADT - Acceptance Deployment Tool (v2)
=====================================

This project automates the deployment of eXo/Meeds products for testing purpose.

Each instance is deployed as an isolated docker compose project, fronted by an
nginx reverse-proxy registered with a Traefik v3 (TCP SNI passthrough) running
on an external docker network. All data is stored in named docker volumes.

Prerequisites
-------------

Mandatory:
  * Docker (with the compose v2 plugin)
  * `yq` (mikefarah/yq v4) in the PATH
  * `jq` in the PATH
  * A Traefik v3 running on a docker network named `reverse_proxy` (deployed by
    your configuration management, e.g. puppet). See `etc/traefik/README` for
    the expected setup.

Optional:
  * `j2` (jinja2-cli) in the PATH - else the `exoplatform/j2cli` docker image
    is used to render templates.
  * `php` >= 7.4 for the dev web-server (`adt.sh web-server`).

Configure
---------

    export ADT_DATA=$HOME/adt_data

You can also define your settings in `$HOME/.adtrc` or `/etc/default/adt`.

TLS certificates (for the per-instance nginx) must be provided via env vars:
  ADT_SSL_CERTIFICATE_FILE / _KEY_FILE / _CHAIN_FILE   (global default)
  MEEDSIO_SSL_CERTIFICATE_FILE / _KEY_FILE / _CHAIN_FILE (for *.meeds.io)

Usage
-----

    usage: ./adt.sh <action>

  deploy            Deploys the instance
  download-dataset  Downloads the dataset for the instance
  dump-dataset      Dumps the instance data into a dataset archive
  import-dataset    Imports a v1 dataset tarball into the instance volumes
  start             Starts the instance
  stop              Stops the instance
  restart           Restarts the instance
  undeploy          Undeploys (deletes) the instance

  start-all         Starts all deployed instances
  stop-all          Stops all deployed instances
  restart-all       Restarts all deployed instances
  undeploy-all      Undeploys (deletes) all deployed instances
  list              Lists all deployed instances

  init              Initializes the environment (frontend network + dashboard)
  update-repos      Update Git repositories used by the web front-end
  web-server        Starts a local PHP web server (dev mode)

Products
--------

  meeds    Meeds.io                                   (Tomcat, docker image)
  plfcom   eXo Platform Community Edition             (Tomcat, docker image)
  plfent   eXo Platform Express/Enterprise Edition    (Tomcat, docker image)

Versions 7.2+ are supported. See `etc/versions.yaml` for the image tag mapping.

Examples
--------

  # Initialize the environment (network + dashboard)
  ./adt.sh init

  # Deploy Meeds 7.2.0-SNAPSHOT on PostgreSQL
  ./adt-dev.sh deploy -n meeds -v 7.2.0-SNAPSHOT -d postgres:17

  # Deploy eXo Platform Enterprise 7.2.0 on MySQL
  ./adt-dev.sh deploy -n plfent -v 7.2.0 -d mysql:8.4

  # List deployed instances
  ./adt.sh list

  # Undeploy an instance
  ./adt-dev.sh undeploy -n meeds -v 7.2.0-SNAPSHOT -d postgres:17

  # Undeploy all instances
  ./adt.sh undeploy-all
